## 📱 MOBILE-FIRST CRITICAL PRIORITY

**IMPORTANT:** 850% of traffic is mobile. This redesign is **MOBILE-FIRST**, desktop is secondary.

### **Mobile Experience Requirements:**

**Performance:**
- Page must load in under 2 seconds on 4G
- Lazy load all images below fold
- Minimal layout shift (CLS score)
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px

**Design:**
- Thumb-zone optimization (important actions within reach)
- Sticky CTA button at bottom on mobile
- Large, tappable elements
- No tiny text (minimum 16px)
- Generous padding/spacing for touch
- Swipeable carousels for related products

**Engagement:**
- Native app-like feel (smooth scrolling, instant feedback)
- Pull-to-refresh feeling (visual feedback on interactions)
- Bottom sheet style modals (not center popups)
- Haptic-feeling animations (bounce, spring physics)
- Social media inspired interactions

**Mobile SEO:**
- Mobile-friendly schema markup
- Fast Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)
- Readable without zooming
- No horizontal scroll
- Touch-optimized navigation

**Test on actual devices:**
- iPhone 12/13/14 (most common)
- Samsung Galaxy S21/S22
- Small screens (iPhone SE)
- Large screens (iPhone Pro Max)

All design decisions must prioritize mobile experience. Desktop is an enhancement, not the baseline.

## ✅ IMPLEMENTATION REQUIREMENTS

### **Technical Constraints:**
- Must use Tailwind CSS (no custom CSS files)
- Can use lucide-react icons
- Server component = ProductPage, Client component = ProductPageContent
- No external animation libraries unless absolutely necessary
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Accessibility: ARIA labels, keyboard navigation
- Performance: Lazy load images, optimize animations

### **SEO Non-Negotiables:**
- ✅ All content must be in DOM (even if visually hidden)
- ✅ Proper heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3)
- ✅ Schema markup unchanged
- ✅ No content in iframes or external scripts
- ✅ Semantic HTML throughout

### **User Experience Goals:**
- Reduce perceived page length
- Increase engagement with interactive elements
- Maintain fast load times
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Mobile-optimized (60%+ traffic)

